        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 10:34PM MDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 1033 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of McDonald, or 11 miles west of Tatum, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tatum, Gladiola, and Tatum Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
